                     <origDate notBefore="1745" notAfter="1800">King Täklä Giyorgis (possibly Täklä Giyorgis I, r. 1779-1800 with interruptions; cf. EAE IV, 826) is mentioned on fol. 70ra. Patriarch ʾabba Marqos and Metropolitan ʾabba Yoḥannǝs are mentioned on fol. 69vb. Mark VII was the patriarch of Alexandria in 1745-69. Yoḥannǝs III was the metropolitan of Ethiopia in 1744-61 (cf. EAE V, 71).</origDate>
